1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object detection and attention estimation in first-person videos. 
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses applications such as augmented reality and driver assistance systems, which are related to human-centered computing. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing videos. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper proposes a novel unified model that incorporates both spatial and temporal evidence. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes a new approach to address the chicken-and-egg problems in object detection and attention estimation.
